description.plain:
Jessie J is a British singer. Born in 1988, she first came to fame when her single, “Do It Like A Dude” hit #2 in the UK. Singles “LaserLight”, “Nobody’s Perfect”, “Who You Are”, “Domino”, and “Price Tag” all hit the Top 10 in the UK, making her the first British female artist to achieve 6 Top 10 singles in the UK. The latter two became Top 25 hits in the US, with “Domino” peaking at #6 and “Price Tag” hitting #23.

Jessie J’s second album, Alive, became a UK-only release. The three singles, “Wild”, “It’s My Party”, and “Thunder” all hit the Top 20 in the UK, with the first two making Top 5. On the album charts, it hit #3 and went gold.

Her third album, Sweet Talker, was released internationally and preceded by the smash single “Bang Bang” featuring Ariana Grande and Nicki Minaj. In the UK, it went straight to the top of the charts, while in the US, it debuted at #6, tying her highest peak. Eventually, it hit #3, becoming Jessie’s highest peak, Grande’s second-highest, and Minaj’s tied-for-highest. (Minaj later surpassed her peak with her number two single, “Anaconda”.) “Bang Bang” also hit the Top 10 in Australia, Canada, Denmark, and New Zealand and went Platinum X6 according to RIIA. The next single, “Burnin' Up” was less successful, although it cracked the Top 100 in both the US and UK. Third single “Sweet Talker” was released in only the UK/Ireland, and fourth single “Masterpiece” hit the US Hot 100, but only managed a 159 peak in the UK.

After 3 years away from the music scene, Jessie came back with a fourth LP, R.O.S.E. (2018). The official single from the album is “Queen” along with two promo singles “Think About That” and “Not My Ex”.

songs.title: Flashlight

description.plain:
Released on April 23, 2015, “Flashlight” is a song written specifically for the Pitch Perfect 2 soundtrack by, among others, Sia Furler and Sam Smith. The hotshot songwriters were picked to pen the first original song of the franchise.

It’s a ballad centered around how someone’s loved one helps them through adversary.

Jessie J was signed up to sing for the soundtrack because she loved the first movie.

songs.title: Price Tag

description.plain:
Released as Who You Are’s second single, “Price Tag” was a huge commercial success, topping the Ireland, New Zealand, and the UK charts (her first #1 in all these countries).

The song is about making music because you want to, not just for the sales and pleasing the people around you. Jessie references this when she says that she writes about her life, and as this song was written at the start of her career, when she first came to America, it reflects her views on her career sort of as a first impression of the lifestyle.

songs.full_title: Domino by Jessie J
songs.title: Domino

description.plain:
“Domino” was the fifth single in Jessie’s debut studio album Who You Are and was released on the 29 August 2011. The song was Jessie’s second UK number one single.

Jessie revealed during an interview with MTV Buzzworthy that her inspiration for this song was the influence of Whitney Houston and Prince. Therefore she wanted to write something “timeless, fun and uplifting”.
